34 permission to take any examination given or
35 required pursuant to sections 324.400 to 324.439;
36 (3) Obtaining or attempting to obtain any
37 fee, charge, tuition or other compensation by
38 fraud, deception or misrepresentation;
39 (4) Incompetency, misconduct, gross
40 negligence, fraud, misrepresentation or
41 dishonesty in the performance of the functions
42 or duties of the profession regulated by
43 sections 324.400 to 324.439;
44 (5) Violation of, or assisting or enabling
45 any person to violate, any provision of sections
46 324.400 to 324.439, or of any lawful rule or
